CFI of Zimbabwe to Sell a Stake in Fertilizer-Maker Windmill, Newsday Says

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-03-25T08:39:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/cfi-of-zimbabwe-to-sell-a-stake-in-fertilizer-maker-windmill-newsday-says.html
CFI Holdings Ltd. (CFI)  of Zimbabwe plans
to sell its 14 percent stake in  Windmill (Pvt) Ltd. , a
fertilizer-maker,  Newsday reported , citing Chief Executive
Officer Steve Kuipa.  CFI, a poultry and retail company, expects to return to
“modest levels of profitability” by its year-end in September,
the Harare-based newspaper said.  Norsk Hydro ASA (NHY)  is a Windmill shareholder, according to the
fertilizer group’s website. Windmill and the Zimbabwe Fertiliser
Co. (Pvt) Ltd. are the southern African nation’s only makers of
compound fertilizers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  